$ /proc/sys/kernel/randomize_va_space

The value of `/proc/sys/kernel/randomize_va_space` controls ASLR (Address Space Layout Randomisation). It should be one of
  • 0: disabled
  • 1: Conservative: Shared libraries and  PIE binaries are randomized.
  • 2: Conservative and start of *brk* area is randomized, too

